															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jonnyd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(248389); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=248389&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182964" alt="JonnyD" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=248389)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jonnyd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(248389); return false;" >JonnyD</a></span> <span class="odate time_1251385762 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">27 Aug 2009 15:09</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-570685">
									

<p>So far SCP-825 has 100% negative rating. Disappointing as I am, I have to concede that there are a lot of problems with it. The basic idea isn't terribly original, the logs are probably too wordy and I think I got distracted by a bunch of different ideas so any ideas of any worth got lost.</p>
<p>I'd like to turn it around if I can, and would welcome any suggestions as to what steps I should take. Ideas I've had:</p>
<ol>
<li>Cut my losses, chalk it up as a learning experience and leave it be as a testimony to my inability to be brief</li>
<li>Decommission it, free up the 825 number for something more worthwhile. I don't know that it would even make a good decommission story, since there's nothing stopping us from just throwing it in a furnace.</li>
<li>Split out the experiment log to its own page. Easy to do, probably won't change much.</li>
<li>Get rid of the experiment log, condense any worthwhile points into the main body (The guy and his sisters, the dog lover, 682 and Clef are the ones I'd like to keep, what do others think?)</li>
<li>Trim down the log (maybe combine with splitting it to its own page). There are probably entries that need to be a lot shorter, or maybe cut completely.</li>
<li>Redesign the function. The whole "Worst Fear" thing allows a lot of variety, but maybe that's the problem. Maybe I should just redesign it to be that it makes you experience attacking and torturing the ones you love most, which I personally thought was the most horrific scenario.</li>
</ol>
<p>Thanks for your help.</p>

