<p>I think you're right about those entries Ghost, I think that they detract from the mood because they're slightly humorous as well. I've gone ahead and commented them out.</p>
<p>I tried to keep the scenario tied to each individual subject rather than allowing the SCP to use past experience. I felt that the inevitable result would be a chaotic mish-mash of every kind of phobia and torture at once. Then again, maybe that would be less effective than something subtle, so that would be an excuse for variety instead of the same "optimized" vision each time.</p>
<p>Although, having more than one subject at the same time (like the accidental application) would open things up for hybrid scenarios.</p>

